Class IdentityTransformerSetupException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • com.deltaxml.api.DeltaXMLException
          • com.deltaxml.core.PipelinedComparatorException
            • com.deltaxml.core.IdentityTransformerSetupException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class IdentityTransformerSetupException
extends PipelinedComparatorException

    Thrown to indicate a problem instantiating or configuring an identity XSLT Transformer.

    The PipelinedComparator makes use of an identity XSLT Transformer in its implementation. If there are problems instantiating or configuring this transformer then this exception may be thrown. The configuration which is performed centres around calls to the JAXP TransformerHandler.getTransformer() and Transformer.setOutputProperty(String, String) methods. These are in turn a consequence of the use of the PipelinedComparator.setOutputProperty(String, String) method.

    The getCause() method should provide details of the underlying TransformerConfigurationException.

    If this exception is encountered we suggest checking your use of the PipelinedComparator.setOutputProperty(String, String) method and that a standards conforming XSLT processor is available on your classpath. If this is the case and there is still a problem please contact DeltaXML support for further assistance.

    See Also:
    TransformerConfigurationException, DeltaXMLException.getCause(), TransformerHandler.getTransformer(), Transformer.setOutputProperty(java.lang.String, java.lang.String), Serialized Form
